caption: Me and my wife was having a hard time finding somewhere to eat one day and was walking around looking at places when we saw this place.  We decided to give it a try and ended up loving the place.  Food was really really good.  It was a very laid back place and ended up being a special night for us.
Quick with big portions.
Was skeptical because the restaurant was empty (it was late) but decided to try it anyway and definitely did not regret it. Pasta was amazing and the staff very friendly
Nasty old food.  Worst cheesecake I've had in my life.  If that is bad, the rest of the food must be bought at the dollar store and left in the freezer for a year.  Gag.
Amazing place for  amazing  food
Amazing food!!! Try the tomato basil soup!!! Customer service was lovely as well.

I have tried this place twice. the pizza was ok the second time I ordered the house salad no tomatoes.  it indicates that it comes with shaved Parmesan cheese and crostini.... I literally got a container of lettuce and dressing. THAT IS IT.... FOR 12 bucks including tip.  like JUST LETTUCE.  And the dressing is legit Italian dressing out of the bottle at the store.  Sad that the Marriott keeps them as room service
Servers helpful and attentive. Food was good and worth the money. I would happily recommend.
The food was amazing and Chris made us feel like ohana (family).
I've been there 5 times this week and every time the food is good and the staff is friendly

Friendly, helpful staff and great food!

Really impressed with the quality of food and the portions, stopped by for supper and had a huge helping of Chicken Parm. Wife had a delicious Chicken Alfredo.  Servers were attentive and helpful, would recommend this to anyone looking for a decent Italian style supper at a good price.
(Translated by Google) The price is ㅡ ㅡ  (Original) 가격이 ㅡㅡ
Great early bird special.
Food was acceptable.  Waitress was friendly and attentive.
Casual eatery, very nice pasta and pizza with friendly staff. A little off the beaten track but a welcome change from the bustle of Waikiki.Prices reasonable.

Tried to go last night only serving pizza and salad no other menu items. Went this a.m. We were 20 minutes early and hostess didn't seem to want to welcome us. Thinking it was whom I spoke to just got sour taste and decided not to return later.
Staff was friendly and accommodating.    Food was tasty and reasonably priced.   Nice atmosphere.
Fantastic service and excellent food, worth a visit.

I came in because it was the closest option, but the service was pleasant and the food surprisingly good. The salad, bread and bolognese sauce were all excellent, and the tiramisu was quite airy-tasty.  This place is not trying to be more than a local American-Italian place, and it excels at that. The wine list is nothing to write home about, but has a couple Italian Chiantis that are good table wines. If youre looking for true Italian food, go elsewhere, but if you like American-Italian, this is the best at this price point you will find. This crushes Olive Garden.
Excellent service and food. Great combination in a tourist area.
I give it 3.5 stars. The wait staff is generally very good. The happy hour prices cant be beat. Food is solid.
Spaghetti is very good. Service was great from Ray. Worth you hard earned money.
Food is good but the service is average
In general, dinner is so-so. The restaurant is expensive and not tasty. I do not advise In addition, a 20% tip is included in the bill.
Very friendly and accommodating staff. Food was great.
(Translated by Google) The spaghetti was fantastic  (Original) 스파게티가 환상적이였어요

Me and my girlfriend visited that place yesterday, we got spaghetti with meatballs and alfredo fettuccini. First one was not that good, but fettuccini was decent, however their servers need to get some lessons, it's super rude to add auto-gratuity to couples.. this should be used for groups of 4+ persons, not for couples, i've been working in restaurant as well for few years - this is rude. I dont care about the 6$ or so, i would left 10+, but that is rude and disrespectful. Never coming back here... Greedy servers.
It was good to have some good food. Although McDonald's and IHOP are close it's worth the extra few dollars.
Good food, quite clean place

Excellent service and food was delicious
Nothing special. Service was fast but wait staff not particularly friendly.
Great for me and my family food was lit closest breakfast joint to the courtyard
Best meatball in all of town. RIGATONI VARY NAICE. Five out of 5
Fast service, good food, Hostess Christin took great care that everything was delightful
Really good pasta. Server was so nice too. We went on Friday night and was chill. Hatd to find thoughtful servers.
Great food, awesome prices, everyone was friendly and welcoming!
Delicious Chicken Marsala! Wonderful, friendly service!
Food was okay but the service was stellar!
Great cocktails and pasta, pizza was nice but could have had a bit more seasoning. Excellent service, would visit again

This place would be a solid 4 stars if not for the bartender having a heavy hand with the liquor. I had the spaghetti and meatballs and was really impressed with the pasta being cooked just right and not overdone. The meatballs and sauce had a really complex flavor that would not be considered a safe dish for children. Also the fact that this restaurant has a short menu is a good sign of quality.

(Translated by Google) Pizza and caprese were delicious! We also recommend you to enjoy early because there is also Happy hour! In addition, because there are terrace seats in stylish atmosphere and open space, you can enjoy pleasant food and drink. I asked for a recommended margherita for pizza. It is recommended because it was very delicious with crispy pizza dough, large tomatoes, and taro cheese. The clerk was also a friendly and good store! Place was great, food was delicious,  price was as expected for good food in Hawaii, employees were great as well! Totally recommend it!
Great wait staff (thank you Chris) and good food
It is located at marriot courtyard. Food is pretty good. If you love a good deal...check out the happy hour!
Great food Grear service

Think twice. The spaghetti and meatballs were flavourless to the point that even my 5 year old daughter wouldn’t eat it, and she lives on spaghetti & meatballs. The $24 pasta and shrimp dish had a total of 5 shrimp. You read it right, 5! There a reason this place ain’t that busy...
The service and people were amazing, but the food was nasty, especially for the price you have to pay.

Good service
Good food  and good prices. Nice waitresses.

Fantastic food and fair price! My group and I have been in Waikiki a week and this was our favorite place. We found it on Yelp and walked up.. a little Underwhelmed at the small hole in the wall look but we decided to go anyway. Drinks were huge, food was HUGE and flavorful. We had several different entrees but the rigitoni bologneese was the favorite. Don’t let the small place fool you. Jonathan was our waiter, very friendly and knowledgeable of the area. Will be back.

This is simply the worst food I’ve ever eaten. We had stale bread. Lasagna that tasted like mush, almost to the point that you don’t have to chew with your teeth (included is a picture of a piece of “lasagna” aka dog food). They were also rushing us the entire time at 6pm on a Wednesday night. They had NO bar selection either. This is a disgrace to all Italian places all over the entire world. So basically don’t come here unless you like your food prechewed, microwaved, stale, and expensive with no alcohol selection to even make it remotely better!! There’s so many better, cheaper places to eat in Waikiki (wheat & barley in the international market place), don’t waste your time! after we left, we went to a place that’s actually palatable... McDonald’s.
Waited by the front door to be seated and every staff member walked by and nobody greeted us or said anything. Waited for a few minutes then left. Would not recommend this place at all!
Amazing food excellent service
Reasonable Happy Hour prices with really good food. Decent breakfast but pricy, I'm happy with lunch and dinner.

This place is a find! Great prices, friendly staff and excellent food. I’m not sure why everyone complained about prices or service. Maybe they are used to McDonald’s?? The Lava Flow drink is a decadent sweet drink, spaghetti pomodoro is delectable and the bruschetta is divine, meatballs are perfect and the chicken piccata melts. Definitely a must go if in the area.
Food and service were great! Very happy with our experience.
Great food and value. Possibly the best meal we've had since arriving here 7 days ago.

I had spaghetti and meet balls.  Served with a piece of bread.  All food well prepared but very little seasoning but the portion was generous.  Restaurant was clean and staff polite. No parking available and prices are kind of on the expensive side.
Brilliant. We arrived just as it was getting busy. Bar Lady was superb (didn't catch her name, short hair, nice ink) food was quick to the table & delicious. Generous portions.

Not very impressed with the food. As for room service, they never are able to deliver to guest rooms because they are understaffed. The food is overpriced and not really worth it. Got sick the 2 times I ate there, never again.
Good Italian food at a decent price
Great place

Tough one to rate, as an Italian I take pride in an authentic Italian cuisine.  I wouldn’t say Spada is that, but the red sauce is pretty good and the pizza was crispy and flavorful.  The bar isn’t set very high for tourist trap Mecca Waikiki, but the early bird hour was a draw for us.  Sadly, still overpriced even with the early bird specials.  I would give a 4 on food and a two on price, but considering everything in Oahu/Waikiki is insanely overpriced I’ll leave be a bit generous with the 4 stars.
Balsamic vinaigrette is awesome but the rest of the food is just ok and over priced.
My husband & I had Spaghetti Puttanesca & Spaghetti Meatballs and it was delicious ! The staff was very friendly and attentive. Will definitely come back !
(Translated by Google) Beer is expensive but food is good  (Original) ビールは高いけど、飯はうまい

I stayed at the Marriott with which the restaurant is attached. It was right there so I decided to try it. I had the fettuccine Alfredo with shrimp, house salad, calamari to start and mai tai. The drink was perfect! Respect to the bartender! The house salad was actually not bad. The vinegarette was tangy. Then came the calamari, which with a little lemon was actually not horrible. The red sauce served with it was plain. No flavor at all. Not even tomatoe flavor like you would think. Then the Alfredo; Bland is not the word! It was lifeless and just took up space. No salt, no pepper, nothing! The shrimp was over cooked which only added to my disappointment of the restaurant. It’s clear that the only reason this restaurant is in business is because of the hotel it is attached to. I hate to leave a bad review but please don’t waste your money on the food here. The drinks however are well worth your money.
Great food and excellent service!  Enjoyed the outdoor seating area very much!!
If you love Lasagna, try this, you'll like it, also pizzas, chicken piccatta etc.. reasonable prices and really good, early bird specials before 7pm, and open for breakfast too also good prices
Laura our server was just a pleasure to have serve us. Great location , great variety of dinner options, great centralized location for people watching:) highly recommended
Good Italian Food
The service was great and the food was so tasty. We went two days in a row because it was.
This is NOT Italian food.  Not sure what to call it.  Over cooked chicken and extravagant prices.  Waitress was confused and the service was extremely slow for whatever reason.
Staying at the adjacent Courtyard by Marriot Hotel, this is where I ate my breakfast. The staff is always welcoming and friendly. Breakfast selection is varied and delicious.
Great food short walk from the hotel
Great food. Easy access from downtown area and walking distance from hotel. Food delicious. Quantity was plentiful. Good price for the food.
Overpriced, poor service, and mediocre food (at best). Considering the other options nearby - you would do better walking another block and trying something else.
Great pizza and wine list
Very very Good joint for me and the wife, romantic, slow music friendly athmospher and salads very fresh, ohh pizza and pastas very well done with a real italian taste,

I had a fettuccine Alfredo with chicken and to be honest I was very disappointed. The Alfredo sauce had no taste; not even the pasta! You could tell that they didn't even salt the water in which the pasta was boiled because even some salt in the pasta water would've have been infused into the pasta and would've been noticeable to those of us with a liking to the taste of salt. I had to add a good amount of salt to get just the slightest hint of taste. I understand that some restaurants may want to limit the salts/ spices used in dishes to accommodate a range of taste profiles but even the most novice of chefs should know that to make a dish a wonderful experience for the person eating it must have.have some flavor to it! Moving on to the chicken... What type of chicken did they use? I honestly felt like I was eating fake chicken. It was hard  and felt more like I was eating a gummy bear that lost its taste and was left out in the sun too long. It was a disappointing dish especially since I've had such great and simple fettuccine Alfredo's in many other restaurants. I feel bad leaving such a bad review but the truth is the truth. As a restaurant you are supposed to provide your customers a gastronomic experience that leaves them happy and  with a slight nostalgia to come back. In this case, I left disappointed and wishing I had eaten somewhere else.

We have ate out for breakfast, lunch and dinner for a week straight now. We started getting real tired of expensive food that tasted either sub-par or downright nasty. We stopped at spada for the early bird dinner special. Price was amazing for the area and the food... Best we've had yet. Service was fantastic. The only negative was no kids menu, granted it doesn't seem the place that wants screaming kids around anyway. (We got lucky with a mellow kid.) But we just ordered our son a cheese pizza and decided to take the leftovers for lunch. The pizza was awesome. Finally a pizza place that doesn't have a strong tomato taste. It was nice, mellow and sweet. 5 stars 6 if I could.
Thank you Sabrina for making our 15th Anniversary special. Such great service and food. I would recommend this little Italian place!

I needed a break from seafood and asian food, so we came here. Pleasantly surprised by the food. I ordered the fettucine Alfredo, and it came out fast, and was nice and hot, though lacking in a little seasoning, an easy fix. I had added meatballs to my order and they were well cooked, filling and tasty. Good portion sizes, our service was great.

We eat here regularly because of the combination of good food, good prices, and good service. Portions are large enough we get a take home box for leftovers. The restaurant is in a hotel, and the restrooms are at the other end of the building.

Food was ok. But service was BAD. The waiter was kind of rushing to clear the table. He cleared the table then gave us the bill. He then asked how much tip we would put on the bill before he will swipe the credit card. We thought he might have a difference kind of credit card machine. As it turned out, he filled  out tip amount on the credit card receipt and just asked us to sign. It is kind of rude. We left the table and  walked till the entrance then we noticed the waiter did not return the credit card to us. We went back and asked for it. He was kind of not seeing an issue on it. We told him to check on the machine. He found the card, return to us, WITHOUT A WORDS OF APOLOGY. NOT recommended to this restaurant.

(Translated by Google) The staff does not speak Japanese, but there is a Japanese menu. Therefore, it may be easy for travelers to enter. When the weather is nice, terrace seats are recommended!  (Original) 店員さんには日本語は通じませんが、日本語のメニューがあります。なので、旅行者には入りやすいかも。 天気の良い日はテラス席がおススメ！
Tasteless and expensive food. Poor service. Water was the best part of our meal.

We liked this place for breakfast as we are staying at the hotel.. prices are reasonable for Honolulu. It was nice to sit by the pool in the morning but the best was our server Ping was a joy and very attentive and gave us some great ideas for local food. We give Ping 5 stars!!! ... but food was good but not great but overall a pleasant morning experience.
(Translated by Google) Even Japanese people can feel free to enter and it is reasonable.  (Original) 日本人でも気軽に入れて、リーズナブルです。

Guys, This is the worst place to eat in Honolulu. Trust me, I am very forgiving when on holiday but I don't know how this "restaurant" is in business. This is not sour grapes,  I just don't want anyone else to waste money here. The foodcourt is so much better or go to Il Pucino which is a bit more expensive but great. Tell.me I'm wrong!

We just ordered a pizza and meatballs! Great service! Great food. Had a wonderful flavor! We have a wonderful pizza place back home that's family owned and highly rated. I think Spada ranks just as high for Waikiki!
Spaghetti & Meatballs were great. So was the baked four cheese pasta.

Was there twice. 1st time - had no expectations. Fantastic pasta pomodoro.  Terrible undrinkable coffee 2nd time - high expectations after the surprisingly good recent dish. Ordered lazagna.  Disaster. Uneatable. Don't know what it was. Left it but paid. Hope it was safe. Will know tomorrow. Only beer and service were really good today. Paid 33$ and went on to eat something.

Pizza was the best ive had by far much better than Giovannas also ordered the garlic bread which I loved but my husband didn't he said it was to buttery ,we came back another night and tried the fettuccine alfredo which my husband loved and I thought was good also better than what I had at Giovannas the night prior and the chicken parm which was very delicious .We plan on going back again our last night here my only complaint would be service is a little slow but the food is worth the wait.
The food was blan I ordered a salad and got a tomato with mozzarella cheese on top of it... that's not a salad. For the cost of the food it was not worth it.
Got full on lemonade as we were waiting for fresh tomatos to grow in the back. Hahaha

They have a early dinning menu from 5:30pm to 7:00pm. We arrived at 6:30pm and the place was about. 75% full. Hostess asked us if we could wait 15min caustic it was busy!! Seated at 6:45pm and walks felt there tell 7:15 got up and left. Had a felling they were trying to run out the clock os the early menu on a bunch of other people too..

We asked to start with a salad but they brought the entree first which was very bland. We cancelled the salad. The wine was almost at the point of going bad. We should have returned it, but we didn't. Very disappointing . We had read the reviews hoping we would have a better experience, but we didn't.
Breakfast croissant sandwich was good. Pizza for dinner was ok, but will not order again. Before dinner they offered stale bread slices with oily balsamic vinegar for dipping.
Simple small menu.  Good Margarita pizza.

Food took over an hour to get, including a simple plate of spaghetti for my kids. I had the burnt sausage and soggy peppers. Managed to overcook the sausage and undercook the pasta. The broccoli that came with it was left untouched as it looked inedible.

Mediocre food. If you think Olive Garden is authentic Italian food, this place shouldn't disappoint too badly. Mediocre staff. Wait staff can't remember a simple order without bollocksing it up. So many better places nearby, it's a wonder how they stay in business. Save your money and go to the McDonald's down the street. It's about as Italian, and they are less likely to screw up your order.  So here's my suggestion if one of the staff read this review: WRITE THE ORDERS DOWN. It's not an onerous task, and will make for far fewer customer complaints.
Good food authentic flavors good
Nice breakfast.
Excellent food. I had the spaghetti and meatballs. Delicious and was piping hot. I will go again.

Absolutely terrible, food is bland and tasteless, my son had a pizza that had "italian sausage" on it that tasted like it was about to go off and that night it made him sick. I had the fettuccini that was supposed to be in a garlic cream sauce and it was tasteless, the chef had used Jerusalem artichoke instead of roasted garlic. When I pointed this out i was told "it's mild garlic", sorry but that's b*llsh*t. My wife had the "four cheese pasta shells" more like "white gunk and leather shells" Certainly no lemon zest or Gorgonzola cheese and it had been baked so long the pasta was hard and tough. I have had far better meals cooked by first year catering students. My wife and I have traveled a lot and this was one of the worst we have ever experienced, AVOID AT ALL COSTS.
This was embarrassing. Food was not very good and way overpriced. Service was lacking.

This place exceeded my expectations based on some of the previous reviews.  The guy who prefers olive garden obviously has a skewed view on "Italian" food.  Our waitress was terrific and upbeat even though the other waitress who was supposed to be working called in sick.  For a laid back quiet place connected to our hotel it was fantastic.

You reviewed in the last week Quality Poor to fair Facilities Good Service Poor to fair  I WILL NEVER SET FOOT IN THIS PLACE AGAIN! Due to the fact that the female manager in the SPADA Restaurant is the most UNPROFESSIONAL manager i have ever encountered. I Have stayed at Marriots all over the world; Paris, California, New York and i was so bothered by the actions of this woman that i shall never return to this location. She was our server the first morning and ignored us as she sat there doing nothing. When she FINIALLY took our order she was rude and snappy erging us to hurry up though there was only 2 other tables. The second morning we had a different female server who was courteous fast and efficient. Half way through our meal our first server who we found out was the manager, screamed at our server rudely in the dinning room in front of all the customers bringing the employee to tears. Public humiliation is usually not the encouragment someone needs especially when the manager was just sitting there doing nothing. You can tell shes an unhappy pesamistic person. 2 employees would eventually quit by the end of our 10 day stay. My experience at other Marriot dining facilities is complete opposite. I take my mom to the mothers day brunch back home in New York every year. I am a travel agent and i shall advise everyone i speak to not to waste their money at this place. plus the food quality is horrible. If i was the owner of this place i would seriously consider change of management unless he wishes to lose more money. This is the most common reason why restaurants fail. The owner is too trusting in management and management becomes power-crazed. Having a dictator in a resteraunt does not work the only way a business runs successfully is if it is run with communication, respect, and understanding. I feel bad for the manager that little bit of power is all she probably has to cling to in her life. she needs a hug.

Worst meal during our extended Waikiki stay.  Meatballs completely bland. Spaghetti undercooked. Sauces desparately need seasoning.  With Arancino at other Marriott you might expect better. Bypass Strada, go to Arancino on Beachwalk instead.

This place is over priced considering its location and atmosphere.  I dont recommend it because for the price...you can have an ellegant meal beachfront.  Kuhio is a noisy and bus laiden street and  the seating is open to a noisy intersection.

Poor food. Poor service. There was no drinks menu when we arrived then the staff took ages to take our drinks order. Our appetizer came after the entree though they did apologise and took it off the bill.  The couple sitting behind us had an even longer wait for their entrees and had repeated apologies from the staff.  I couldn't even say that the food was good (it was OK) and overall I would say that it was poor value.
